The Senator representing Kogi West Senatorial District in the National Assembly, Dino Melaye, on Monday described Big Brother Naija (BBNaija) 1st runner up, Mike Olayemi Edwards as a moral compass for all African young persons. The Senator also said that he respects the 28-year-old with profound regard, adding that he owes him. Melaye, in a tweet on his official Twitter page wrote: “Mike of BBN is a model of an ideal young Nigerian. “I respect him with profound regard. I am proud of him as a moral compass for all African young persons. I owe him.” DAILY POST reports that Mercy emerged winner of BBNaija ‘Pepper Dem’ edition on Sunday after scoring highest votes. She defeated Mike, Frodd, Seyi and Omashola to emerge winner of reality TV show. Mercy had trounced Mike, Frodd, Omashola, and Seyi, the top five BBNaija housemates, who contested for the bragging rights of the reality TV show’s season 4 with a whooping 20.5m votes representing about 41.77 percent of the total votes cast.  Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.